				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\rho &gt; \omega_{\alpha }$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M228"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>ρ</mml:mi><mml:mo>&gt;</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>ω</mml:mi><mml:mi>α</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="41598_2022_15762_Article_IEq110.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, however, if an isoform or a sgRNA has outlier and overlapped datasets or big noises, then <inline-formula id="IEq111"><alternatives><tex-math id="M229">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
