      <p id="Par13">Although CRISPR sgRNAs and RNA isoforms occur at sub-gene level, a set of CRISPR sgRNAs targeting a set of DNA sequences of a gene was already designed before experiment, the variation of RNA reads of sgRNAs is fixed or due to a fixed effect, while the variation of isoform RNA reads is uncertain, depends on gene structure such as alternative poly(A) sites, alternative splicing sites in UTR, exons, introns, in other words, due to the random effect. This factor has not been considered in the current methods. To use the information on this factor, we introduce gene-wise <inline-formula id="IEq112"><alternatives><tex-math id="M231">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
