      <p id="Par32">In another experiment, we simulated count data of splicing events in two samples using negative binomial generator in R environment based on pasilla exon splicing count data where there are 69,733 exons distributed within 14,206 <italic>Drosophila</italic> genes. Control sample has 4 biological replicates and knockdown sample has 3 biological replicates. In the all four scenarios, NBBt-test outperformed DEXSeq and had F1-score = 100% and the observed FDR = 0 from FDR = 0 to 0.1 (Supplementary Fig. <xref rid="MOESM2" ref-type="media">S8</xref>), while DEXSeq had F1-score = 44% and the observed FDR = 0.65 from FDR = 0 to 0.1(Supplementary Fig. <xref rid="MOESM2" ref-type="media">S8</xref>).</p>
