				\begin{document}$$\tau = UA$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M500"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>τ</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mi>U</mml:mi><mml:mi>A</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="41598_2022_15762_Article_IEq236.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> to 10% and 30% null poly(A) isoforms where U is uniform variable (<inline-formula id="IEq237"><alternatives><tex-math id="M501">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
